article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 59, Albany, N.Y. 14
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Jeremy Moses threw for 313 yards and three touchdowns to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 59-14 victory against Albany on Saturday. Fifteen players caught at least one pass for the Lumberjacks (1-1), who pounced on the Great Danes (1-1) immediately. Graly Crawford returned the opening kickoff for a touchdown and caught a scoring pass from Moses as Stephen F. Austin built a 25-7 lead after the first quarter. Crawford had seven receptions for 55 yards. Anthony Foster, Corde Roberson and Lance Dozier also caught TD passes. Moses completed 28 of 37 attempts with an interception. Dan Di Lella was 21 of 36 for 173 yards and ran for a touchdown for Albany, whose coach, Bob Ford, turned 73 on Saturday.
